From 5b5595f1948408db79fdd4c3d60b792d7ad421a1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jithender Kondam <jreddy@marvell.com>
Date: Tue, 3 Feb 2026 07:57:31 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] Add WRED profile binding CLI command (config qos
 wred-profile)

Description:
Implement new `config qos wred-profile` subcommand group to bind and manage
WRED profiles on interface queues. This feature enables runtime binding of
WRED profiles to specific queues without requiring configuration file edits.

Features:
- config qos wred-profile bind <profile> <interface> <queue_spec>
  Bind WRED profiles to interface queues with flexible queue specification
  support (single: "3", range: "1-4", comma-separated: "1,3,5",
  mixed: "0-2,5,7-9"). Replaces existing profiles and binds valid queues
  with warnings for invalid queue indices.

- config qos wred-profile unbind <interface> <queue_spec>
  Remove WRED profile bindings from interface queues using same queue
  specification formats.

- show qos wred-profile [interface] [queue_spec]
  Display all current WRED profile bindings across interfaces with optional
  filtering by specific interface.

Backward Compatibility:
- No breaking changes to existing commands or APIs
- Existing ecnconfig command continues to work as before
- New CLI provides alternative interface for WRED profile management

Signed-off-by: Jithender Kondam <jreddy@marvell.com>
